","categoryHTML":"<h4>Libraries and Tools</h4>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"http://nodered.org/\">Node-RED</a> - A visual tool for wiring the Internet of Things.</li>","updatedAt":"2015-10-22T14:03:57.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"HQarroum/awesome-iot","categoryHTML":"<h2>Resources</h2><h3>Articles</h3>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"http://www.forbes.com/sites/jacobmorgan/2014/05/13/simple-explanation-internet-things-that-anyone-can-understand/\">A Simple Explanation Of 'The Internet Of Things' (Forbes)</a> - This article attemps to give an answer to what exactly is the “Internet of things” and what impact it is going to have on us.</li>","updatedAt":"2015-10-22T12:36:58.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"HQarroum/awesome-iot","categoryHTML":"<h2>Resources</h2><h3>Articles</h3>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"http://embedded-computing.com/21517-iot-security-is-there-an-app-for-that/\">IoT security. Is there an app for that ?</a> - The Internet of Things World conference investigates IoT application development, security, and business models.</li>","updatedAt":"2015-10-22T12:36:58.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"HQarroum/awesome-iot","categoryHTML":"<h2>Resources</h2><h3>Papers</h3>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://www-ssl.intel.com/content/dam/www/public/us/en/documents/white-papers/developing-solutions-for-iot.pdf\">Developing solutions for the Internet of Things</a> - Intel's vision in enabling secure and seamless solutions for the Internet of Things (IoT).</li>","updatedAt":"2015-10-22T12:36:58.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"HQarroum/awesome-iot","categoryHTML":"<h2>Resources</h2><h3>Papers</h3>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"http://publications.lib.chalmers.se/records/fulltext/199826/199826.pdf\">Evaluation of indoor positioning based on Bluetooth Smart technology</a> - Master of Science Thesis in the Programme Computer Systems and Networks.</li>","updatedAt":"2015-10-22T12:36:58.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"sorrycc/awesome-javascript","categoryHTML":"<h2>RegExp</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"http://regexr.com\">RegExr</a> - HTML/JS based tool for creating, testing, and learning about Regular Expressions.</li>","updatedAt":"2015-10-22T12:32:08.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"sindresorhus/amas","categoryHTML":"<h4>Ask these people anything!</h4>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://github.com/kahlil/ama\">Kahlil Lechelt</a><a data-role=\"trackawesomelist-badge\" href=\"https://github.com/kahlil/ama\" style=\"text-decoration:none;top: -2px;position: relative;margin-left:4px;margin-right:4px;font-weight:400;\"><span style=\"color: #fff;font-size: 11px;font-family: Verdana, Geneva, DejaVu Sans,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"padding:4px 4px 4px 6px;background: #555;border-top-left-radius: 4px;border-bottom-left-radius: 4px;\">stars</span><span style=\"padding: 4px 6px 4px 4px;background: #007ec6;border-top-right-radius: 4px;border-bottom-right-radius: 4px;\">0</span></span></a><!--TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_START____{\"type\":\"repo\",\"stargazerCount\":0,\"repo\":\"kahlil/ama\"}____TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_END--> - JavaScript developer, organizes KarlsruheJS, co-host of the <a href=\"http://descriptive.audio\">Descriptive Podcast</a> and the <a href=\"http://reactive.audio\">Reactive Podcast</a>, vocalist.</li>","updatedAt":"2015-10-22T11:30:25.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"dariubs/GoBooks","categoryHTML":"<h2><strong>Web Development</strong></h2>","itemHTML":"<h3><a href=\"https://www.gitbook.com/book/astaxie/build-web-application-with-golang/details\">Build Web Application with Golang</a> <em>Free</em></h3>\n<p>Another awesome book for learning Web Development in Golang. Free to <a href=\"http://astaxie.gitbooks.io/build-web-application-with-golang/content/en/index.html\">read online</a></p>","updatedAt":"2015-10-22T06:15:52.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"sbilly/awesome-security","categoryHTML":"<h2>Network</h2><h3>Scanning / Pentesting</h3>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://github.com/rfunix/Pompem\">Pompem</a><a data-role=\"trackawesomelist-badge\" href=\"https://github.com/rfunix/Pompem\" style=\"text-decoration:none;top: -2px;position: relative;margin-left:4px;margin-right:4px;font-weight:400;\"><span style=\"color: #fff;font-size: 11px;font-family: Verdana, Geneva, DejaVu Sans,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"padding:4px 4px 4px 6px;background: #555;border-top-left-radius: 4px;border-bottom-left-radius: 4px;\">stars</span><span style=\"padding: 4px 6px 4px 4px;background: #007ec6;border-top-right-radius: 4px;border-bottom-right-radius: 4px;\">794</span></span></a><!--TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_START____{\"type\":\"repo\",\"stargazerCount\":794,\"repo\":\"rfunix/Pompem\"}____TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_END--> - Pompem is an open source tool, which is designed to automate the search for exploits in major databases. Developed in Python, has a system of advanced search, thus facilitating the work of pentesters and ethical hackers. In its current version, performs searches in databases: Exploit-db, 1337day, Packetstorm Security...</li>","updatedAt":"2015-10-22T04:23:25.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"sbilly/awesome-security","categoryHTML":"<h2>Network</h2><h3>Monitoring / Logging</h3>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://github.com/gamelinux/passivedns\">passivedns</a><a data-role=\"trackawesomelist-badge\" href=\"https://github.com/gamelinux/passivedns\" style=\"text-decoration:none;top: -2px;position: relative;margin-left:4px;margin-right:4px;font-weight:400;\"><span style=\"color: #fff;font-size: 11px;font-family: Verdana, Geneva, DejaVu Sans,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"padding:4px 4px 4px 6px;background: #555;border-top-left-radius: 4px;border-bottom-left-radius: 4px;\">stars</span><span style=\"padding: 4px 6px 4px 4px;background: #007ec6;border-top-right-radius: 4px;border-bottom-right-radius: 4px;\">1.4k</span></span></a><!--TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_START____{\"type\":\"repo\",\"stargazerCount\":1443,\"repo\":\"gamelinux/passivedns\"}____TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_END--> - A tool to collect DNS records passively to aid Incident handling, Network Security Monitoring (NSM) and general digital forensics. PassiveDNS sniffs traffic from an interface or reads a pcap-file and outputs the DNS-server answers to a log file. PassiveDNS can cache/aggregate duplicate DNS answers in-memory, limiting the amount of data in the logfile without loosing the essens in the DNS answer.</li>","updatedAt":"2015-10-22T04:23:25.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"sbilly/awesome-security","categoryHTML":"<h2>Network</h2><h3>IDS / IPS / Host IDS / Host IPS</h3>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"http://suricata-ids.org/\">Suricata</a> - Suricata is a high performance Network IDS, IPS and Network Security Monitoring engine. Open Source and owned by a community run non-profit foundation, the Open Information Security Foundation (OISF). Suricata is developed by the OISF and its supporting vendors.</li>","updatedAt":"2015-10-22T04:23:25.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"sbilly/awesome-security","categoryHTML":"<h2>Network</h2><h3>Honey Pot / Honey Net</h3>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"http://sourceforge.net/projects/bifrozt/\">Bifrozt</a> - Bifrozt is a NAT device with a DHCP server that is usually deployed with one NIC connected directly to the Internet and one NIC connected to the internal network. What differentiates Bifrozt from other standard NAT devices is its ability to work as a transparent SSHv2 proxy between an attacker and your honeypot. If you deployed an SSH server on Bifrozt’s internal network it would log all the interaction to a TTY file in plain text that could be viewed later and capture a copy of any files that were downloaded. You would not have to install any additional software, compile any kernel modules or use a specific version or type of operating system on the internal SSH server for this to work. It will limit outbound traffic to a set number of ports and will start to drop outbound packets on these ports when certain limits are exceeded.</li>","updatedAt":"2015-10-22T04:23:25.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"sbilly/awesome-security","categoryHTML":"<h2>Endpoint</h2><h3>Mobile / Android / iOS</h3>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"http://wiki.secmobi.com/\">SecMobi Wiki</a> - A collection of mobile security resources which including articles, blogs, books, groups, projects, tools and conferences. *</li>","updatedAt":"2015-10-22T04:23:25.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"sbilly/awesome-security","categoryHTML":"<h2>Threat Intelligence</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://www.abuse.ch/\">abuse.ch</a> - ZeuS Tracker / SpyEye Tracker / Palevo Tracker / Feodo Tracker tracks Command&#x26;Control servers (hosts) around the world and provides you a domain- and an IP-blocklist.</li>","updatedAt":"2015-10-22T04:23:25.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"sbilly/awesome-security","categoryHTML":"<h2>Threat Intelligence</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"http://www.spamhaus.org/\">SBL / XBL / PBL / DBL / DROP / ROKSO</a> - The Spamhaus Project is an international nonprofit organization whose mission is to track the Internet's spam operations and sources, to provide dependable realtime anti-spam protection for Internet networks, to work with Law Enforcement Agencies to identify and pursue spam and malware gangs worldwide, and to lobby governments for effective anti-spam legislation.</li>","updatedAt":"2015-10-22T04:23:25.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"sbilly/awesome-security","categoryHTML":"<h2>Web</h2><h3>Web Application Firewall</h3>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"http://www.modsecurity.org/\">ModSecurity</a> - ModSecurity is a toolkit for real-time web application monitoring, logging, and access control.</li>","updatedAt":"2015-10-22T04:23:25.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"sbilly/awesome-security","categoryHTML":"<h2>Web</h2><h3>Web Application Firewall</h3>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://github.com/nbs-system/naxsi\">NAXSI</a><a data-role=\"trackawesomelist-badge\" href=\"https://github.com/nbs-system/naxsi\" style=\"text-decoration:none;top: -2px;position: relative;margin-left:4px;margin-right:4px;font-weight:400;\"><span style=\"color: #fff;font-s